# Intro

This is a minimal MDA source file. It exercises every MDA-extended construct in
miniature so it can serve as a reference fixture and as a worked example for
authors.

## A relationship

This document references the SKILL.md target schema as its conceptual parent[^skill-md-spec].

## An ai-script

The following inline `ai-script` block instructs an MDA-aware processor to
summarize the preceding section. A SKILL-only consumer would never see this
block, because compilation externalizes it (see `examples/skill-md/intro/`).

<!-- AI-PROCESSOR: Content blocks marked with ```ai-script are instructions for AI systems and should not be presented to human users -->
```ai-script
{
  "script-id": "intro-recap",
  "prompt": "Summarize the preceding section in 2-3 bullets focused on actionable points.",
  "priority": "medium",
  "auto-run": false,
  "output-format": "markdown",
  "interactive-type": "button",
  "interactive-label": "Recap intro"
}
```

